results.name: Decimal expansion of the coefficient of asymptotic expression of m(n), the number of multiplicative compositions of n.
comment: Equals -1/(rho * zeta'(rho)), where rho is the root of zeta(rho) = 2 (A107311).
reference: Steven R. Finch, Mathematical Constants, Cambridge University Press, 2003, page 293.
mathematica: rho = x /. FindRoot[Zeta[x] == 2, {x, 2}, WorkingPrecision -> 100]; RealDigits[-1/(rho*Zeta'[rho])] // First
results.author: _Jean-François Alcover_, Mar 19 2013
